enumMember.description:
The additional information are inserted in textual format.
Such information are added depending on printout type as per below DTD schema.In case of alarm printouts::type=<type>, [exchange=<exchange>,] [networkid=<networkid>,] [cpname=<cpname> ,] cpside=<cpside>, device=<device> , prca=<prca>, prseqno=<prseqno> , altype=<altype>, allevel=<allevel> , alcls=<alcls>, alcat=<alcat> , alseqno=<alseqno>, alno=<alno> , alvisno=<alvisno>[, sessid=<sessid> ] [, cmdid=<cmdid>];In case of spontaneous printouts:
:type=<type>, [exchange=<exchange>,] [networkid=<networkid>,] [cpname=<cpname> ,] cpside=<cpside>, device=<device> , prca=<prca> [, sessid=<sessid> ] [, cmdid=<cmdid>];

In case of result and restart printouts:
:type=<type>, [exchange=<exchange>,] [networkid=<networkid>,] [cpname=<cpname> ,] cpside=<cpside>, device=<device> [, sessid=<sessid>] [, cmdid=<cmdid> ];
